<sec id="summary">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <p>Brightway is an open source framework for Life Cycle Assessment
  (LCA) calculations in Python. The combination of a modular structure,
  the expressiveness and interactivity of Python and in particular
  Jupyter notebooks, and tuned calculation pathways allows for new
  research directions in Life Cycle Assessment. Brightway has been used
  in papers on meta-analysis of many inventory datasets
  (<xref alt="Wernet et al., 2011" rid="ref-wernet2011environmental" ref-type="bibr">Wernet
  et al., 2011</xref>), regionalized LCA
  (<xref alt="C. L. Mutel et al., 2011" rid="ref-mutel2011gis" ref-type="bibr">C.
  L. Mutel et al., 2011</xref>), and sensitivity analysis
  (<xref alt="C. L. Mutel et al., 2013" rid="ref-mutel2013two" ref-type="bibr">C.
  L. Mutel et al., 2013</xref>). Brightway consists of three main
  modules: Brightway2-data
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2012c" rid="ref-bw2data" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2012c</xref>) manages how data is stored and accessed;
  Brightway2-calc
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2012b" rid="ref-bw2calc" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2012b</xref>) does static and Monte Carlo calculations; and
  Brightway2-IO
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2015c" rid="ref-bw2io" ref-type="bibr">C. Mutel,
  2015c</xref>) handles the import and export of LCA data from various
  sources. In addition to these libraries, helper libraries provide
  documentation and application examples
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2012a" rid="ref-brightway2" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2012a</xref>), support for parameterized inventories
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2015b" rid="ref-bw2parameters" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2015b</xref>), and a format for LCA data in arrays
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2013" rid="ref-statsarrays" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2013</xref>). A web page
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2016" rid="ref-homepage" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2016</xref>), documentation
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2015a" rid="ref-bw2docs" ref-type="bibr">C.
  Mutel, 2015a</xref>), and a development blog
  (<xref alt="C. Mutel, 2014" rid="ref-blog" ref-type="bibr">C. Mutel,
  2014</xref>) are also available.</p>
</sec>
